oc:kn_1176254c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:directiveContent "[Company]_Initiation_Report_[Date].docx — the ONLY deliverable. Do NOT create summaries, next-steps docs, or completion reports." ;
    oc:templateVariables "Company",
        "Date" .

oc:kn_12327548 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Complete Task 5 assembly workflow" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Verify all prerequisites (Tasks 1-4 complete). 2. Extract charts from zip, organize working directory. 3. Read Task 1 .md file and Task 3 .md file. 4. Extract tables from Excel via XLSX skill. 5. Write quantitative sections (Financial Analysis, Projection Assumptions, Scenario Analysis, Valuation). 6. Write synthesis sections (Investment Thesis, Risk Assessment, Price Target). 7. Copy Task 1 Company 101 content verbatim with inline charts. 8. Copy Task 3 valuation analysis with inline charts/tables. 9. Write Page 1 Investment Summary LAST. 10. Add appendices with clickable hyperlinks. 11. Run quality checklist. 12. Deliver DOCX file." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_135557ff a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "All report assembly outputs" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Report must meet minimum specifications: 30+ pages, 10,000+ words, 25+ embedded charts, 12+ comprehensive tables. Projection Assumptions must be 2,000-3,000 words and Scenario Analysis must be 1,500-2,000 words." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These minimums define institutional-quality equity research. Falling below them produces a document that is not client-ready." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_2438fc81 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SideEffect ;
    oc:appliesToContext "File operations during assembly" ;
    oc:directiveContent "This task reads Task 1 .md, Task 2/3 .xlsx, Task 3 .md, and Task 4 .zip files. It writes one new .docx file. It does NOT modify any existing files." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Read-only access to prior task outputs ensures no corruption of source data. The single output file is the final deliverable." ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_2f78274e a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before beginning assembly" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verify all 4 mandatory charts exist before starting: (1) Revenue by Product stacked area, (2) Revenue by Geography stacked bar, (3) DCF Sensitivity heatmap, (4) Valuation Football Field. Also verify statistical summary rows in comparable companies table." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These charts are non-negotiable visualizations that anchor the financial and valuation analysis sections. Missing any makes the report incomplete." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_43527dd8 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When assembling the full report layout" ;
    oc:directiveContent "A good equity research report is text-dense with lots of illustrating images. Target 60-80% page coverage. Insert charts every 200-300 words. Charts must be interspersed throughout, NOT grouped at end." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Professional institutional research reports are information-dense with visuals breaking up text. Grouping charts at the end or having text-only pages is amateurish." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_462ac304 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:directiveContent "Page 1: INITIATING COVERAGE header | Thesis title | Rating box (rating, current price, target, 52-wk range, market cap, EV) | Analyst info | Stock chart (Figure 1) | 3-4 ■ bullets with bold headers | Financial summary table (years with A/E suffixes). Pages 2-5: Thesis & Risks. Pages 6-17: Company 101. Pages 18-30: Financial Analysis. Pages 31-40: Valuation. Pages 41-50: Appendices." ;
    oc:templateVariables "52_week_range",
        "analyst_name",
        "company_name",
        "current_price",
        "enterprise_value",
        "market_cap",
        "rating",
        "recommendation",
        "target_price",
        "thesis_title" .

oc:kn_51654821 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PostFlightValidation ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After assembling the complete report" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Run the full quality checklist before delivery: verify page count (30-50), word count (10,000-15,000), chart count (25-35), table count (12-20), all URLs are clickable hyperlinks, all numbers match the financial model exactly." ;
    oc:hasRationale "This is the final deliverable of a multi-task workflow. Any quality failure reflects on the entire research effort. Do not deliver if any check fails." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_62c0bb5a a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "All written sections of the report" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Lead with numbers in all writing. Use 'vs.' not 'versus'. Format years as 2024A (actual) and 2025E (estimate). Use $X.XB for billions, $XXXM for millions. Basis points for margin changes. Active voice. Be specific and quantified." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Institutional equity research follows specific conventions. Generic language like 'strong growth' is unacceptable — always quantify." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_86be76d9 a oc:Command,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When extracting financial data for report tables" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use XLSX skill to open [Company]_Financial_Model_[Date].xlsx and read tabs: Revenue Model, Income Statement, Scenarios, DCF, Sensitivity Analysis, Comparable Companies" .

oc:kn_9d33ddf3 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing Page 1 Investment Summary bullets" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use ■ character for Page 1 bullets. Format: ■ **Bold Topic Header.** Followed by 3-5 sentences with specific numbers and quantification. Example: ■ **Vertical SaaS leadership should enable $50bn+ TAM by 2030.** Deep domain expertise... 95%+ net revenue retention..." .

oc:kn_aca2584d a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When assembling Company 101 sections (pages 6-17)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do NOT rewrite Task 1 company research content (6-8K words). Use it almost verbatim — just reformat from markdown to Word and insert charts inline. Focus original writing effort on quantitative sections." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Task 1 content is already professional analysis. Rewriting wastes tokens and risks introducing errors. The value-add in Task 5 is the quantitative interpretation and investment thesis." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b8fec2ad a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When assembling the DOCX in the most efficient order" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Phase A: Create DOCX structure + Page 1 (write last). Phase B: Copy Task 1 content + insert charts (40-50% of report). Phase C: Write financial analysis with data from Excel (30-40%). Phase D: Add valuation from Task 3 (mix of copy + tables). Phase E: Appendices + references. Phase F: Write Page 1. Phase G: TOC + page numbers." ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

oc:kn_b9182a86 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any report section" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never use placeholder language like 'this section would include...', 'charts would be inserted here...', or 'see model for details...'. Write every section in full, embed every chart, extract every table." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Placeholders indicate incomplete work and undermine the credibility of the research. Institutional investors make million-dollar decisions based on these reports." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_ce024a95 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always — Task 5 cannot run without all prior task outputs" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Requires completed Task 1 (company research .md, 6-8K words), Task 2 (financial model .xlsx, 6 tabs), Task 3 (valuation analysis .md + 4 Excel tabs), Task 4 (charts .zip, 25-35 PNG files). All files must be accessible." .

oc:kn_dc385a3c a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before starting Task 5" ;
    oc:directiveContent "ALL four prior tasks (1: company research, 2: financial model, 3: valuation analysis, 4: charts) MUST be complete before starting Task 5. Stop immediately if any prerequisite is missing." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Task 5 is a pure assembly task — it cannot generate missing content. Starting without all inputs produces incomplete, unprofessional output." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

